&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h2 data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;About Crunchyroll&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Founded by fans, Crunchyroll delivers the art and culture of anime to a passionate community. We super-serve over 100 million anime and manga fans across 200+ countries and territories, and help them connect with the stories and characters they crave. Whether that experience is online or in-person, streaming video, theatrical, games, merchandise, events and more, it’s powered by the anime content we all love.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join our team, and help us shape the future of anime!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Overview&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an experienced Accountant Director to lead the accounting operations for our entity in India, with 2 locations in Hyderabad (90% of employees) and Mumbai (10% employees) and liaising with the General accounting team located in Melbourne (Australia) or GBS team in Dallas/LosAngeles, mostly in charge of accounts payable process.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This critical role ensures the integrity of financial reporting, compliance with local regulations (IndaGAAP and IFRS), and adherence to global policies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Accountant Director supervises all local GAAP financials, local tax, local audit, accounting reporting processes, and actively supports strategic decisions and the implementation of global policies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position reports to the Senior Accounting Director of the Rest of World.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Financial Reporting &amp;amp; Compliance&lt;/strong&gt;Work closely and provide adhoc analysis to the General accounting team in Melbourne in charge of IFRS postings preparation and approval .&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure strict compliance with Local GAAP, local tax laws, regulatory requirements, and SOX controls.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare all documentation requested in accordance with SOX, ICFR and other controls&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate general ledger records and oversee reconciliation processes in local gaap&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare financial statements under Indian Companies act&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage local tax filings, statutory reporting, and audits, acting as the key liaison with global accounting teams (Consolidation, Tax) and the General accounting team in Australia.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement and maintain robust internal controls to protect company assets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Accounting Operations &amp;amp; Treasury &amp;amp;tax&lt;/strong&gt;Prepare the calculation and invoicing related to transfer pricing and funds requests aligned with intercompany agreements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure FEMA compliance, reporting, documentation, and coordination with banks/RBI&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure execution of closings, focusing on tax, local GAAP adjustments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review or manage tax filings, GST VAT tax returns , withholding declaration, direct and indirect tax CSR and other in an accurate manner in collaboration with tax advisor and global tax team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure fixed assets are created in a timely manner in accordance with the capitalization rules ( costs to be capitalized or not), and the capex budget is accurate and communicated in a timely manner to the general accounting team in Melbourne.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure all vendor invoices are communicated to Accounts payable team in a timely &amp;amp; exhaustive manner&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure revenues and costs are aligned with the budget&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure accruals are exhaustive and accurate, invoiced, paid in a timely manner ( intercompany, marketing, T&amp;amp;E) transactions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Estimate funds needed in order to ensure vendors are paid in a timely manner&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow the credit limit of Amex credit card in order to ensure employees can

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h2 data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;About Crunchyroll&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Founded by fans, Crunchyroll delivers the art and culture of anime to a passionate community. We super-serve over 100 million anime and manga fans across 200+ countries and territories, and help them connect with the stories and characters they crave. Whether that experience is online or in-person, streaming video, theatrical, games, merchandise, events and more, it’s powered by the anime content we all love.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join our team, and help us shape the future of anime!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;About the Role&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Category Manager-Localization supports sourcing and procurement activities across Crunchyroll&#39;s Localization category, including Subtitling/Captioning, Dubbing (English and International), Creative Localization, and Accessibility (CC/AD).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role focuses on executing sourcing events, analyzing vendor proposals, coordinating contract reviews, and maintaining supplier performance data in partnership with senior sourcing leadership.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll collaborate closely with the Director of Strategic Sourcing, the Localization leadership team, and cross-functional partners in Content Operations, Legal, and Finance to help ensure our localization services deliver value, quality, and speed for fans around the world.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You Will&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support execution of sourcing initiatives for localization services such as dubbing, subtitling, and accessibility, rate benchmarking, and contract negotiation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct vendor and market research, prepare rate comparisons, and analyze spend data to identify potential savings and efficiency opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute sourcing events and RFx processes in partnership with senior sourcing leaders, ensuring stakeholder alignment, documentation accuracy, and timely completion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Draft and manage MSA/SOW templates with guidance from Legal; track redlines, ensure version control, and finalize documentation for execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain supplier data, rate cards, and purchase order accuracy in procurement systems; monitor spend trends and report key metrics for assigned categories.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track supplier KPIs such as on-time delivery, cost performance, and quality feedback, preparing reports and dashboards for business reviews.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Localization, Content Operations, and Marketing Localization teams to route requests correctly and support intake prioritization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in forecasting and capacity planning, compiling data to inform seasonal volume ramps and resource allocation decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate process improvements and reporting for procurement transactions, compliance tracking, and supplier onboarding.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We get excited about candidates like you because…&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have 5+ years of experience in Strategic Sourcing, Procurement, or Category Execution, ideally in media localization, post-production, or creative services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have hands-on experience running RFPs, supporting negotiations, and performing vendor analysis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;re comfortable working with procurement systems (Coupa or similar) and tracking spend accuracy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have strong Excel/Sheets skills and can build clear, data-driven cost comparisons and reporting dashboards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You understand localization and post-production workflows (dubbing, subtitling, accessibility) and are eager to deepen your expertise in these categories.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;re familiar with MSA/SOW templates and contract c

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h2 data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;About Crunchyroll&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Founded by fans, Crunchyroll delivers the art and culture of anime to a passionate community. We super-serve over 100 million anime and manga fans across 200+ countries and territories, and help them connect with the stories and characters they crave. Whether that experience is online or in-person, streaming video, theatrical, games, merchandise, events and more, it’s powered by the anime content we all love.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join our team, and help us shape the future of anime!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Crunchyroll is the ultimate home for anime worldwide, connecting millions of fans through streaming, theatrical releases, events, gaming, and beyond. As we accelerate our growth across Asia, we are seeking a Communications Senior Manager, Asia to lead regional communications strategy, strengthen Crunchyroll&#39;s brand reputation, and drive impactful storytelling that connects anime fans, media, partners, and industry stakeholders across diverse markets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Communications Senior Manager, Asia, you will be responsible for developing and leading the communications strategy across emerging markets and opportunities to support broader regional initiatives. You will serve as the regional communications lead, shaping how Crunchyroll&#39;s brand, content, executives, and business priorities are represented across media, industry, and fan communities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role requires a strategic communications leader who can operate at both the corporate and consumer level—driving visibility for major anime launches, theatrical releases, partnerships, and fan experiences while also protecting and enhancing Crunchyroll&#39;s reputation across the region.&amp;nbsp; You will act as a trusted advisor to regional leadership, provide executive communications counsel, lead crisis and issues management efforts, and oversee a network of agency partners across multiple markets.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting to the Marketing Director - SEA, this role will play a critical leadership role in shaping Crunchyroll&#39;s communications strategy and long-term growth across Asia.&amp;nbsp; The role will work closely with the Global Communications team, including the SVP, Communications, Senior Director of Corporate Communications, and the Director of Regional Communications &amp;amp; Strategy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will be remotely based in Singapore.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and execute Crunchyroll&#39;s communications strategy across Asia, aligning regional initiatives with business, brand, and marketing objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive integrated communications campaigns for anime title launches (SVOD), theatrical releases, brand campaigns, partnerships, fan experiences, and corporate initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop compelling narratives and culturally relevant storytelling that strengthen Crunchyroll&#39;s brand leadership and fan engagement across diverse Asian markets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a strategic communications advisor to regional leadership, supporting corporate communications, executive visibility, and key business announcements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead crisis communications and issues management, providing counsel and response strategies for reputational, regulatory, and operational matters.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain strong relationships with media across entertainment, lifestyle, business, and including anime communities and pop culture press, driving high-quality coverage through compelling storytelling, press outreach, and talent opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Localize global campaigns with Asian cultural relevance to resonate with regional audiences and media landscapes.&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h2 data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;About Crunchyroll&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Founded by fans, Crunchyroll delivers the art and culture of anime to a passionate community. We super-serve over 100 million anime and manga fans across 200+ countries and territories, and help them connect with the stories and characters they crave. Whether that experience is online or in-person, streaming video, theatrical, games, merchandise, events and more, it’s powered by the anime content we all love.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join our team, and help us shape the future of anime!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Crunchyroll, LLC is an independently operated joint venture between US-based Sony Pictures Entertainment, and Japan&#39;s Aniplex, a subsidiary of Sony Music Entertainment (Japan) Inc., both subsidiaries of Tokyo-based Sony Group Corporation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;As the Content Acquisitions Associate, you will secure a pipeline of content to satisfy Crunchyroll&#39;s seasonal simulcast slate and catalog lineups, while strengthening its relationships with our Japanese partners&#39; teams and augmenting our reputation as the most trusted international distributor for Japanese anime abroad.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Core Areas of Responsibility&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contact Japanese and international partners to receive the latest information on their production schedule and discuss opportunities to grow and foster our distribution partnership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Foster relationships with Japanese partners and manage account relationships, including daily business.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with other departments to deliver top tier service for our partners and to ensure that contractual obligations are performed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Acquire in-depth knowledge of our business in each internal department to address important issues, situations, industry trends, and market dynamics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain an open dialogue with licensors to respond to requests, bid submissions, and help implement solutions and reporting of our activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with the Content Evaluation team to assess the value of content.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with the Business Affairs team to close contracts and secure delivery of assets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with the Marketing team to procure marketing materials needed to support successful title launches.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;In the role of Content Acquisitions Associate, you will report to the Director, Content Acquisitions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are considering applicants for the location of Tokyo, Japan.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We get excited about candidates, like you, because...&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years of experience in successful account management, partner management, business development, or licensing sales experience in Entertainment or Anime industry.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in establishing and nurturing long-term, mutually beneficial partnerships, working with a Japanese client base.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience negotiating with partners to represent organizational interests.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience winning a high percentage of the targeted content.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience dissecting proposals and legal agreements surrounding IP.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Native to Business level Japanese language skills (speaking/reading/writing)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Native to Business level English language skills (speaking/reading/writing)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working within a globally matrixed organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building creative solutions in an evolving business environment and media landscape.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h2 data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;About Crunchyroll&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Founded by fans, Crunchyroll delivers the art and culture of anime to a passionate community. We super-serve over 100 million anime and manga fans across 200+ countries and territories, and help them connect with the stories and characters they crave. Whether that experience is online or in-person, streaming video, theatrical, games, merchandise, events and more, it’s powered by the anime content we all love.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join our team, and help us shape the future of anime!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;About the Team&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Data Services team is focused on building robust, scalable, and efficient data services, pipelines, lakes, tools, libraries, and software components that drive best practices and empower service teams to succeed. We design and implement data services, pipelines and data lakes for operational analysis, ensuring they are production-ready with automation and standardized access controls.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We lead and evangelize the principle of 100% automation. Additionally, we establish best practices, provide training, and document data architectures to ensure our systems are reliable, future-ready, and capable of continuous evolution and process improvement across the organization.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About the Role&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Crunchyroll is growing and changing, presenting unique challenges and opportunities to support millions of anime fans around the world. The Data Engineering team provides seamless help to our internal stakeholders, ensuring an exceptional experience for all Crunchyroll fans.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Software Engineer, you will play a pivotal role in designing, implementing, and optimizing data services, ensuring that our data services support the needs of the business. You will also collaborate with cross-functional teams to enhance eventing systems, and develop tools that empower our data and services teams. Your expertise will also be critical in driving 100% automation, best practices, creating scalable services, and optimizing our data environments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Areas of Responsibility&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write clean, maintainable, and well-documented API and code while adhering to industry best practices, including code reviews and design patterns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and resolve performance bottlenecks, ensuring that both frontend and backend components are optimized for speed and reliability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the automation and optimization of build, deployment, and monitoring processes to support a smooth development lifecycle.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain comprehensive test suites (unit and integration) to ensure system reliability and robustness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement and maintain security best practices, safeguarding sensitive data and ensuring compliance with relevant standards and regulations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be proficient in both TypeScript and Python&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, build, and maintain scalable applications/services using TypeScript and Python and modern backend frameworks (Node.js preferred).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build event-driven architectures and event interfaces using AWS services such as SNS/SQS, EventBridge, Kinesis, or Kafka.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep understanding of AWS Processing Framework like Step Functions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Architect and optimize database schemas and queries for relational (RDS PostgreSQL, MySQL), NoSQL (DynamoDB) and Graph Database (Neo4j).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with service engineers, data engineers, and product teams to deliver high-quality software solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
