&lt;p&gt;Join our team, and help us shape the future of anime!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;About the role&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are hiring a Director of Engineering, Monetization Platform to join the Service Monetization organization and lead the long-term platform investment required to scale Crunchyroll’s monetization systems for future growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting to the Vice President of Engineering, Service Monetization, this leader will own strategy and execution for the shared monetization foundation across platform scalability, reliability, observability, compliance, service modernization, architectural simplification, infrastructure efficiency, and high-ROI refactoring of critical systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Their mission will be to help Crunchyroll’s platform scale to 50M fans by strengthening the monetization systems that support subscription growth, revenue operations, and dependable fan experiences at global scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is intentionally platform-first rather than feature-first. It exists to create the conditions for our product-facing domains to move quickly while ensuring the monetization foundation remains dependable, scalable, secure, and aligned to the company’s long-term growth ambitions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This leader will also partner closely with Data Insights and Enterprise Technology organizations to ensure Service Monetization data, services, controls, and operational foundations reliably support internal business operations across reporting, finance, accounting, and compliance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are considering applicants for Hyderabad, India. This team is intended to serve as a strategic center of excellence for long-term monetization platform engineering while remaining tightly connected to global partners and business needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a unique opportunity for an experienced engineering leader who enjoys building strong organizations, driving platform strategy, and improving the reliability and leverage of systems that are directly tied to revenue and company scale.&lt;/p&gt;
